"n.山崩；压倒性胜利 【英】 n. 山崩；压倒性胜利(ov erwhelming victory) 【考】 deluge : droplet / landslide : peddle(大暴雨:小水滴/ 山崩:小卵石) 【记】 组合词:land(地)+sli de(滑行)→地向下滑 →山崩 n. 崩塌的泥石; 压倒性胜利 【记】land地, slide滑－地向下滑－山崩的大石头. 【类】deluge: droplet = landslide: peddle大暴雨对小水滴 = 山崩的大石头对小卵石(程度类比) 【记】land slide landslide (n.)  1856, American English, from land (n.) + slide (n.). Earlier was landslip, still preferred in Britain. Old English used eorðgebyrst in this sense; literally ""earth-burst."" In the political sense, landslide ""lopsided electoral victory"" is attested from 1888."
